data.description: First time on the market! Lookout Mountain Eastern Brow home with city lights view. Built in 1890, the home has been in the family for multiple generations and still has the original hardwoods and tile, many of the original light fixtures, plaster walls and ceilings, arched doorways, claw-footed tubs and plumbing fixtures and quirky charm you only find from this era. It is now ready for a new owner to come in and restore it to its former glory or take advantage of this great location and view and build something of their own. The home's main level has a traditional floor plan with a dedicated foyer, living room, family room with access to the rear deck, a large dining room, kitchen and master bedroom with a full bath. The upper level has 2 bedrooms, 2 hall baths and a large sunroom with fantastic views. The basement was partially finished at some point and once housed a bedroom, bonus room and full bath, but now it is just being used for storage. There are 2 covered front porches which are perfect for enjoying the activity around historic Point Park next door, and the community offers a wonderful environment for getting out and walking and/or visiting with neighbors. Whether you are looking for a renovation project or the perfect brow lot, then this could be the property for you. Home is being sold As-Is. Please call for more information and to schedule your private showing. Information is deemed reliable but not guaranteed. Buyer to verify any and all information they deem important.
